    "date": "2021-05-07T16:44:22Z",
    "text": "Mens Rea Reform Act of 2021 This bill establishes a default mens rea standard (i.e., state of mind requirement) for federal criminal offenses\u2014statutory and regulatory\u2014that lack an explicit standard.\n\nThe government must generally prove that a defendant acted willfully with respect to each element of an offense for which the text does not specify a state of mind."
